---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Supporters"
  description="The people, institutions, and organizations who believe in what Ryzo Studios is building — and help make it possible."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="supporters-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <span class="eyebrow">Our Supporters</span>
      <h1 class="display">
        The people<br />
        who <span class="accent-text">believe.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-body">Ryzo Studios exists because of individuals, institutions, and organizations who believe that story is still the most powerful system for shifting culture — and that the next generation deserves stories built for where they actually live.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GET INVOLVED — impact investors CTA -->
  <section class="section get-involved-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="get-involved-inner">
        <div class="get-involved-text">
          <span class="eyebrow">Get Involved</span>
          <h2 class="subheadline">Ryzo is ready to scale<br /><span class="accent-text">with impact investment.</span></h2>
          <p class="body-lg">We're building an Impact Franchise Studio — multi-platform story worlds that meet young people inside gaming, animation, and digital community to engage with the big questions of their time. If you believe culture shifts through story, we'd love to talk.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="get-involved-cta">
          <a href="mailto:Erica@ryzo.studio,Todd@ryzo.studio?subject=Impact%20Investor%20Here" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Connect with the team →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OUR APPROACH -->
  <section class="section approach-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Our Approach</span>
      <h2 class="subheadline">Systems of engagement,<br />built where culture actually lives.</h2>
      <p class="body-lg approach-body">The world changed. Kids didn't. They're still searching for stories that get them, spaces where they belong, questions worth caring about. Ryzo builds those systems of engagement inside the platforms where young people actually live — because that's where culture shifts now.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GRATITUDE -->
  <section class="section gratitude-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">With Gratitude</span>
      <h2 class="subheadline">The people and organizations<br />who made this possible.</h2>
      <p class="body-lg gratitude-intro">We are supported by many kinds of people and organizations — early believers, technical collaborators, community backers, and research partners. Each one made the work more possible.</p>

      <div class="gratitude-grid">

        <!-- Block 1: Lead Partners -->
        <div class="gratitude-block featured">
          <span class="gratitude-label">Lead Partners — Rage Fighters</span>
          <div class="partner-name-large">Equimindo &amp; the Caring Masculinity Fund</div>
          <p class="partner-detail">The most significant contribution to the Rage Fighters game came from Equimindo and the Caring Masculinity Fund. Our first franchise centers on boys' coming of age and belonging — and they were true partners in that work, helping us connect with allies around the world and bringing genuine collaborative enthusiasm to the challenge of uniting story and activation inside the places where young people already live.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Block 2: Technical Partners -->
        <div class="gratitude-block">
          <span class="gratitude-label">Technical Partners</span>
          <div class="partner-name-large">AutoDesk · Unreal · Perforce</div>
          <p class="partner-detail">We've received significant software support from AutoDesk, Unreal Engine, and Perforce — tools that power our production pipeline and make it possible for a studio our size to work at the quality level the stories deserve.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Block 4: Community Supporters -->
        <div class="gratitude-block community-block">
          <span class="gratitude-label">Community Supporters</span>
          <h3 class="community-headline">The ones who showed up first.</h3>
          <p class="partner-detail">We have a robust community of supporters who helped us through the early stages of the studio via crowdfunding campaigns on Kickstarter and private donations. Their belief — before the proof points existed — made everything else possible.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BOTTOM CTA -->
  <section class="section-sm become-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="become-inner">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Join Us</span>
          <h2 class="subheadline">Your name<br />on this page.</h2>
          <p class="body-lg">If you believe that young people deserve stories built for where they actually live — stories that are genuinely great and genuinely matter — we'd love to talk.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="become-cta">
          <a href="/connect" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Connect With Us →</a>
          <p class="become-note">All support inquiries are handled personally by the founding team.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .supporters-hero {
    min-height: 70vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding-block: 8rem 5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 40% 30%, rgba(124, 92, 191, 0.12) 0%, transparent 50%),
      linear-gradient(to right, #080316, #1c0832);
  }

  /* Shared background for all sections */
  .section,
  .section-sm {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #080316 0%, #1c0832 100%);
  }

  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .hero-content .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .display { font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 9vw, 8rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .accent-text { color: var(--accent); }
  .hero-body { font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 520px; }

  /* Get Involved */
  .get-involved-section {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }

  .get-involved-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .get-involved-text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .get-involved-text .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .get-involved-cta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: flex-end;
  }

  /* Approach */
  .approach-section {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }

  .approach-section .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .approach-section .subheadline { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .approach-body { max-width: 680px; }

  /* Gratitude */
  .gratitude-section .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .gratitude-section .subheadline { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  .gratitude-intro {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
    color: var(--fg-2);
  }

  .gratitude-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .gratitude-block {
    padding: 3rem;
    background: var(--bg-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .gratitude-block.featured {
    border-top: 2px solid var(--accent);
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .community-block {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .gratitude-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .partner-name-large {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .community-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .partner-detail { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.7; }

  /* Bottom CTA */
  .become-section {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }

  .become-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .become-inner > div:first-child {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .become-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .become-note { font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--fg-3); max-width: 260px; line-height: 1.5; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .get-involved-inner,
    .become-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
    .get-involved-cta { justify-content: flex-start; }
    .gratitude-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .gratitude-block.featured,
    .community-block { grid-column: 1; }
  }
</style>
